        <interface_type>Command-Line</interface_type>
        <interface_type>GUI</interface_type>
        <category>Visualization</category>
        <supported_operating_system_note>OSX, Linux, Windows</supported_operating_system_note>
        <system_requirements_note>Just a reasonably modern O/S and a reasonably fast graphics board.</system_requirements_note>
        <description>SPICE-Enhanced Cosmographia provides a 3D visualization of solar system geometry and of mission geometry, including spacecraft trajectory and orientation, instrument field-of-view frustum, and instrument footprints at times of observations. Cosmographia uses SPICE files to provide most of this geometry information. Configuration of Cosmographia is accomplished using JSON payloads, while user control of Cosmographia is accomplished through a set of standard widgets. A Python scripting interface is also available.</description>
